18:31.218 --> 18:34.176
( panting )

18:40.135 --> 18:43.176
What?

18:45.343 --> 18:50.135
No? Oh. Well, okay.

18:50.218 --> 18:51.385
Okay, then.

18:51.468 --> 18:54.718
Eh, gentlemen, give us a minute.

18:59.760 --> 19:03.010
I thought you were going
to this famous "Walmart."

19:03.094 --> 19:04.593
Overrated.

19:07.052 --> 19:11.677
Are you okay?
We have a salad course.

19:11.760 --> 19:14.260
Would you like a salad course?

19:14.343 --> 19:16.802
I--I don't need
a salad course. Um...

19:16.885 --> 19:19.593
( clears throat )

19:19.677 --> 19:23.260
I'm very flattered.

19:23.343 --> 19:27.052
You're an incredible singer,
and dancer...

19:27.135 --> 19:28.718
and rapper.

19:31.593 --> 19:34.426
There's still an elephant
in the room, though.

19:36.385 --> 19:39.510
Excuse me just a moment.

19:42.802 --> 19:43.802
( door closes )

19:43.885 --> 19:46.218
What's his real name?

19:46.301 --> 19:48.552
You're still on that?

19:48.635 --> 19:50.969
I don't understand,

19:51.052 --> 19:53.969
our emails were so promising.

19:54.052 --> 19:55.301
I know what it's like.

19:55.385 --> 19:56.885
- You do?
- Sure.

19:56.969 --> 19:59.635
Being pampered by
a charismatic leader
in a hotel room...

19:59.718 --> 20:02.552
where maybe even he thinks
he's in love with you.

20:02.635 --> 20:05.010
Plus, power is intoxicating.

20:05.094 --> 20:07.260
- So is vodka.
- Isn't that what dates are for?

20:07.343 --> 20:10.718
You squint at things
and try to see the best
in a guy.

20:10.802 --> 20:14.802
I like giving people
the benefit of the doubt. I do.

20:16.218 --> 20:18.260
Wait, are you in character
right now?

20:18.343 --> 20:19.426
Often. I lose track.

20:19.510 --> 20:22.426
You didn't even Google him?

20:22.510 --> 20:24.802
I didn't think I needed to.

20:24.885 --> 20:26.385
We'd been emailing for months.

20:26.468 --> 20:27.301
I thought--

20:27.385 --> 20:28.552
Girl, it's not that hard.

20:28.635 --> 20:29.969
Especially after Crimea.

20:30.052 --> 20:31.927
When I walked in here,

20:32.010 --> 20:33.885
he was wearing a wedding ring.

20:33.969 --> 20:35.593
But when I checked again,
he wasn't.

20:35.677 --> 20:37.677
And then
I swear he just was.

20:37.760 --> 20:42.176
He can be a little bit
indecisive about
his self-presentation.

20:44.010 --> 20:47.426
Girl. Seriously,
what are you doing?

20:47.510 --> 20:51.176
I don't know.

20:51.260 --> 20:53.927
You know what,
you're a grown woman.

20:54.010 --> 20:55.176
Figure it out.

20:56.635 --> 20:58.844
( door opens and closes )

20:58.927 --> 20:59.760
( sighs )

20:59.844 --> 21:04.468
Alas, Nathan Ivanovich.

21:04.552 --> 21:08.094
I never knew you.

21:10.343 --> 21:15.426
I don't know what is,
only what seems to be.

21:16.760 --> 21:18.552
Or not to be.

21:19.844 --> 21:22.927
How do we even hold up
this heavy life,

21:23.010 --> 21:26.844
which I myself have had
a hand in reducing

21:26.927 --> 21:29.927
down to bare survival?

21:30.010 --> 21:31.552
Survival.

21:33.343 --> 21:36.969
Survival sucks,
but it is possible

21:37.052 --> 21:40.218
death is worse.

21:43.635 --> 21:48.052
Of all the things
I have been party to,

21:48.135 --> 21:51.510
I, who have the power

21:51.593 --> 21:55.510
to bend the course of history,

21:55.593 --> 21:58.885
have come up
against a problem--

22:01.176 --> 22:04.052
one small woman...

22:04.135 --> 22:06.593
and who to be to her.

22:10.552 --> 22:13.552
I should be real to her.

22:15.094 --> 22:18.593
Unless I am corroded
to my depth.

22:21.844 --> 22:24.927
I am out of scale.
I feel myself so.

22:28.969 --> 22:31.176
I should give it a whirl.

22:35.635 --> 22:39.301
( door opens )

22:45.176 --> 22:48.301
Are you married?

22:49.426 --> 22:52.301
Well, yes and no.

22:52.385 --> 22:53.677
( sighs )

22:53.760 --> 22:55.260
I just Googled you.

22:55.343 --> 22:57.552
And if I'm not mistaken,

22:57.635 --> 22:59.635
you have a wife.

23:00.802 --> 23:02.552
You can Google me?

23:02.635 --> 23:04.718
Yeah. I can.

23:04.802 --> 23:06.593
It was pretty easy, too.

23:06.677 --> 23:09.844
It would've been easier if you
didn't have so many pseudonyms.

23:09.927 --> 23:12.468
Hmm.

23:12.552 --> 23:16.635
So, do you and your wife
have some sort of arrangement?

23:16.718 --> 23:19.552
Eh, yes and no.

23:19.635 --> 23:22.052
What's that
supposed to mean?

23:22.135 --> 23:23.927
Well, I mean, sort of.

23:24.010 --> 23:25.260
There's no sort of.

23:25.343 --> 23:27.385
Either you're married
or you aren't,

23:27.468 --> 23:29.969
or your wife and you have
an arrangement or you don't.

23:30.052 --> 23:31.385
Don't get upset.

23:31.468 --> 23:33.052
I'm not upset.

23:36.052 --> 23:38.510
I just need to know.

23:38.593 --> 23:41.969
I mean,
I'm not above casual sex,

23:42.052 --> 23:45.844
but I think we both know
that's not why we're here.

23:47.885 --> 23:51.844
I really liked writing to you
and I like talking to you

23:51.927 --> 23:56.885
and now we're in a hotel room
and I need to know.

24:03.718 --> 24:07.718
Why didn't you ask me before
about being married.

24:07.802 --> 24:10.052
Because you checked
the box.

24:10.135 --> 24:11.135
What box?

24:11.218 --> 24:14.135
The one about
being single.

24:14.218 --> 24:16.260
Oops.

24:16.343 --> 24:17.260
( sighs )

24:20.176 --> 24:23.094
Did you lie about
the sex questions, too?

24:23.176 --> 24:27.385
No. No, no, no, no.
Of course not. Never.

24:27.468 --> 24:29.635
It would mess up the algorithm.

24:29.718 --> 24:32.301
( sighs )

24:32.385 --> 24:35.010
What's the point of having
a girlfriend or a mistress

24:35.094 --> 24:37.010
or whatever it is
you want me to be

24:37.094 --> 24:38.885
if you're just gonna act
the same way you do

24:38.969 --> 24:41.260
at home, or at work,
or whatever?

24:42.760 --> 24:44.593
I know.

24:44.677 --> 24:48.094
This is the tragedy of my life.

24:48.176 --> 24:49.969
( scoffs )

24:50.052 --> 24:52.885
Do you know
the tragedy of my life?

24:54.969 --> 24:56.094
No.

24:56.176 --> 24:58.426
I know.
Because you never asked me.

24:58.510 --> 25:00.010
You're really charming
on the internet,

25:00.094 --> 25:01.510
but then in person,
you don't even ask me

25:01.593 --> 25:03.343
shit like what's
the tragedy of my life

25:03.426 --> 25:05.969
or even if
my parents are alive.

25:06.052 --> 25:07.802
I know your parents are alive
because it came up

25:07.885 --> 25:11.677
in the email when you
went back to Wisconsin.

25:11.760 --> 25:14.010
For my dad's funeral.

25:16.718 --> 25:19.135
This is not my first language.

25:22.260 --> 25:27.385
Don't you even wanna try being
honest just for like one day,
like for an experiment?

25:27.468 --> 25:30.426
- ( stammers )
- ( scoffs )

25:30.510 --> 25:34.552
Look, I need to be
around someone real,

25:34.635 --> 25:37.260
and, Darla,
I can feel that about you.

25:37.343 --> 25:40.010
You are so freaking real.

25:40.094 --> 25:43.385
And... all I do
is create chaos--

25:43.468 --> 25:45.052
which is remarkably
effective--

25:45.135 --> 25:47.010
but you are actually,
truly real.

25:47.094 --> 25:49.426
And that-that
is what I need.

25:49.510 --> 25:51.010
That is why I am here.

25:51.094 --> 25:53.635
I'm sorry.
I... I'm gonna go.

25:53.718 --> 25:55.468
No, no, no, no, no!
Please, please.

25:55.552 --> 25:57.969
Please stay
just for a little longer.

25:58.052 --> 26:00.094
Hey, stay for dessert.

26:00.176 --> 26:01.593
A wonderful
white chocolate mousse.

26:01.677 --> 26:04.343
I need to go. Oh, my God.

26:04.426 --> 26:06.426
( speaking Russian )

26:06.510 --> 26:10.176
No, no, no, they are saying
that it is not safe for you

26:10.260 --> 26:13.426
to leave because
there is a... wildfire.

26:13.510 --> 26:15.844
I don't see any wildfire.

26:15.927 --> 26:17.885
( speaking Russian )

26:21.677 --> 26:23.927
Oh, yes. They are saying
there is a shooting.

26:24.010 --> 26:25.593
It's not safe for you to go.

26:25.677 --> 26:27.593
I didn't hear any shooting,
did you?

26:27.677 --> 26:31.260
Some threat of shooting
or a bomb threat
or something like that.

26:31.343 --> 26:33.885
I don't believe you.

26:33.969 --> 26:36.718
- ( jiggling doorknob)
- All right.

26:36.802 --> 26:38.969
Oh, my God!

26:39.052 --> 26:41.094
They lock it from the outside?

26:42.885 --> 26:45.301
No, no, please,
please relax.

26:45.385 --> 26:46.635
( sighs )

26:46.718 --> 26:49.010
You'll break the knob.

26:49.094 --> 26:51.635
Thank you for staying.

26:51.718 --> 26:55.301
It means a lot to me.

26:55.385 --> 27:00.426
There is so much to say
about the tragedy of my life.

27:00.510 --> 27:02.010
And from your writing,

27:02.094 --> 27:06.635
I believe you will really
be able to understand the pains

27:06.718 --> 27:08.135
that come from being

27:08.218 --> 27:11.969
such an important
political technologist.

27:12.052 --> 27:15.385
You see, it started
when I was a child.

27:18.260 --> 27:21.677
At the academy
in the mountains,

27:21.760 --> 27:25.218
the Ural Mountains.

27:25.301 --> 27:29.176
- They can be beautiful...
- ( sighs )

27:29.260 --> 27:31.426
but they can be deadly.

27:31.510 --> 27:34.426
( old-world sounding anthem
playing )

28:33.635 --> 28:35.468
-♪ (LOW BASS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪
-(SIZZLING)

28:36.010 --> 28:38.802
Thank you for doing what
nobody else seems to understand.

28:39.135 --> 28:41.260
I'm excited for this,
and for my turn next.

28:41.343 --> 28:43.343
It didn't hurt much at all,
by the way.

28:43.426 --> 28:47.343
Oh. Shall we,
before it gets cold? (LAUGHS)
